@node WHATIS "What is PKTGen ?"

        This  program  is  part  of  the  "Monalisa"  project and
        consists  in  a  series of other programs that, together,
        can  perform  powerful  and  flexible  operations  within
        FidoNet  and other Networks.  Read Monalisa documentation
        for more details.

        PKT-Generator  is, as the name suggests, a FidoNet Packet
        Generator.  In detail, you can use PktGen to send mail to
        other  systems,  to  your  system's  points  or  even  to
        yourself.  PktGen is able to send private NetMail as well
        as  public  conference messages.  PktGen respects all FSC
        standards  and  so  far,  I  haven't  found a mailer that
        couldn't import packets from it.

@endnode
@node HOW2USE "How to use"

        You  can  invoke  PktGen  both from Workbench or CLI.  If
        you're  using  CLI,  type  'PktGen ?' for a brief list of
        arguments.   From Workbench, just take a look at PktGen's
        icon  information.   PktGen is an highly flexible program
        with  lots  of  option so that the user can customize his
        own  output.   You  can use PktGen's features by having a
        default  preferences  file  in your Monalisa:Preferences/
        directory  or any other directory you wish as long as you
        tell  PktGen  where  to  find  it.  This is a list of the
        current PktGen parameters:

         @{"[FROM=From]" link FROM}                  @{"[OA=Origin_Address]" link OA}
         @{"[TO=To]" link TO}                      @{"[DA=Destination_Address]" link OA}
         @{"[SUBJ=Subject]" link SUBJ}               @{"[QUIET]" link QUIET}
         @{"[FILE=Message_File]" link FILE}          @{"[NOLF]" link NOLF}
         @{"[TAGN=Echo_TagName]" link TAGN}          @{"[NETMAIL]" link NETMAIL}
         @{"[ORIGL=Origin_Line]" link ORIGL}          @{"[UPDATEFLO]" link UPDATEFLO}
         @{"[MDIR=Storage_Directory]" link MDIR}     @{"[MSGLOCAL]" link MSGLOCAL}
         @{"[CONF=Configuration_File]" link CONF}    @{"[NOTLAST]" link NOTLAST}
         @{"[PKT=Packet_Name]" link PKT}            @{"[REPLYADDR=E-Mail Reply Ad." link REPLYADDR}
         @{"[NOREPLYADDR]" link NOREPLYADDR}                @{"[MSGPRIVATE]" link MSGPRIVATE}
         @{"The Configuration File" link CONFIGFILE}
@endnode
